# MAGIC ## 10. Quick Reference
# MAGIC
# MAGIC | Operation | Code |
# MAGIC |-----------|------|
# MAGIC | Import all types | `from pyspark.sql.types import StructType, StructField, StringType, ...` |
# MAGIC | Define flat schema | `StructType([StructField('col', StringType(), True), ...])` |
# MAGIC | Define nested schema | `StructField('addr', StructType([StructField('city', StringType(), True)]), True)` |
# MAGIC | Array of structs | `StructField('items', ArrayType(StructType([...])), True)` |
# MAGIC | Access nested field | `col('parent.child')` or `'parent.child'` in select |
# MAGIC | Filter on nested field | `df.filter(col('parent.child') == 'value')` |
# MAGIC | Flatten struct | Select each sub-field with `.alias()` |
# MAGIC | Build struct from flat cols | `struct(col('a').alias('x'), col('b').alias('y'))` |
# MAGIC | Parse JSON string col | `from_json(col('json_col'), schema)` |
# MAGIC | Struct to JSON string | `to_json(col('struct_col'))` |
# MAGIC | Explode array | `explode(col('array_col')).alias('item')` |
# MAGIC | DDL nested syntax | `'customer STRUCT<name: STRING, tier: STRING>'` |
# MAGIC | Rebuild struct (update) | `withColumn('s', struct(col('s.a'), col('s.b'), lit('new').alias('c')))` |

